@startuml seq-view-analytics
title Analytics Dashboard Flow

actor "Admin" as Admin
participant "AdminController" as API
participant "AnalyticsService" as Analytics
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

Admin -> API: GET /admin/analytics/overview\n{dateFrom, dateTo}
API -> Analytics: getOverviewMetrics(dateRange)

Analytics -> DB: SELECT COUNT(*) views\nGROUP BY date
DB --> Analytics: views per day

Analytics -> DB: SELECT contentId, COUNT(*)\nORDER BY count DESC LIMIT 10
DB --> Analytics: top 10 popular content

Analytics -> DB: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT profileId)\nGROUP BY date
DB --> Analytics: active users per day

Analytics -> DB: SELECT AVG(duration)\nFROM watch_events
DB --> Analytics: avg engagement time

Analytics --> API: {viewsByDay, popularContent,\nuserGrowth, avgEngagement}
API --> Admin: analytics dashboard data

Admin -> API: GET /admin/analytics/content/{id}\n{dateFrom, dateTo}
API -> Analytics: getContentMetrics(contentId, dateRange)
Analytics -> DB: aggregate events\nfor specific content
DB --> Analytics: content-specific metrics
Analytics --> API: {totalViews, uniqueViewers,\navgWatchTime, completionRate}
API --> Admin: content analytics detail

@enduml
